# CI/CD Pipeline

## Workflow Structure
```
validate.yml (on: push/PR to main)
  ├── backend-checks
  │     ├── ruff check .
  │     ├── mypy app/
  │     ├── bandit -r app/
  │     └── pytest --cov=app --cov-fail-under=80
  ├── frontend-checks
  │     ├── pnpm lint
  │     ├── pnpm typecheck
  │     └── pnpm test
  └── security-audit
        ├── pip-audit
        └── npm audit --production

deploy.yml (on: workflow_dispatch)
  ├── Inputs: environment (production/staging)
  ├── Optional: run checks first
  └── Build container → push registry → deploy platform
```

## Rules for GitHub Actions Changes
- Never skip CI steps without team approval
- Database migration checks must stay: run migrations on CI against fresh DB
- Secrets via GitHub repository/environment secrets — never hardcoded
- `concurrency` group prevents duplicate workflow runs (cancel-in-progress: true)

## Merge Rules
- Squash merge to `main` only
- All jobs in `validate.yml` must be green before merge
- Branch protection enforced on `main`

## Deploy
- Manual trigger only via `workflow_dispatch`
- Always run with validations enabled for production
- Keep environment-specific secrets isolated per environment
- Build immutable Docker images and deploy by digest/tag
